## 1. YouTube

### Primary Sources
- **Data API v3 Docs:** https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3
- **Live Streaming API:** https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3/live/docs
- **Analytics API:** https://developers.youtube.com/analytics
- **API Console / Quota:** https://console.cloud.google.com
- **OAuth 2.0 Guide:** https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/oauth2

### What It Is
Three separate APIs that together cover the full YouTube lifecycle. They don't automatically talk to each other — you wire them.

---

### YouTube Data API v3

**What it does:** Read and write access to YouTube content — videos, playlists, channels, comments, search.

**Auth:**
- Public read-only data → API key (simple)
- User data or writes → OAuth 2.0 (requires consent flow)

**Quota:**
- Default: **10,000 units/day**
- Each API call costs units (e.g., search = 100 units, video insert = 1,600 units)
- Quota increase available via Google Cloud Console request
- Quota resets at midnight Pacific

**Key Endpoints:**

| Endpoint | Method | Units | What It Does |
|---|---|---|---|
| `videos.list` | GET | 1–3 | Fetch video metadata, stats, status |
| `videos.insert` | POST | 1,600 | Upload a video |
| `videos.update` | PUT | 50 | Edit title, description, tags, privacy |
| `playlists.list` | GET | 1 | List playlists |
| `playlistItems.insert` | POST | 50 | Add video to playlist |
| `commentThreads.list` | GET | 1 | Read top-level comments |
| `commentThreads.insert` | POST | 50 | Post a comment as authenticated user |
| `search.list` | GET | 100 | Search YouTube — expensive, use sparingly |
| `channels.list` | GET | 1 | Channel metadata, stats |
| `subscriptions.list` | GET | 1 | Check if user is subscribed |

**OIS Use Cases:**
- After stream ends: auto-update video description with session notes from Notion
- Auto-add VODs to "Streams" or "ONCE Writing Sessions" playlists
- Pull subscriber count for weekly Notion dashboard
- Check if new members are YouTube subscribers (subscriber verification flow)

---

### YouTube Live Streaming API

**What it does:** Create and control live broadcasts programmatically. Read live chat messages. Monitor SuperChat events.

**Auth:** OAuth 2.0 required for all live operations.

**Key Concepts:**
- **LiveBroadcast** — the broadcast event (has scheduled start, status, etc.)
- **LiveStream** — the RTMP stream object (the actual video ingestion point)
- **LiveChatMessage** — chat messages during broadcast
- **LiveChatModerator** — moderator management

**Key Endpoints:**

| Endpoint | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `liveBroadcasts.list` | Get broadcast status (active, complete, etc.) |
| `liveBroadcasts.transition` | Start / stop / test broadcast |
| `liveBroadcasts.update` | Edit broadcast settings (title, description, privacy, **made for kids**) |
| `liveChatMessages.list` | Poll live chat (polling required — no push) |
| `liveChatMessages.streamList` | **Server-streaming low-latency chat** (official gRPC-based method — lower latency than polling) |
| `liveChatMessages.insert` | Post a chat message as the channel |
| `liveChatModerators.insert` | Add a chat moderator |
| `liveChatBans.insert` | Ban a user from chat |
| `superChatEvents.list` | Read SuperChat/SuperSticker events |

**Important — Made For Kids:**
The `madeForKids` field lives on `liveBroadcasts` resource. It resets between broadcasts. The pre-stream checklist must verify `madeForKids: false` via API — or check manually. This is the root cause of the March 4 stream incident.

**Live Chat — Two Methods:**
- `liveChatMessages.list` — polling. Response includes `pollingIntervalMillis` telling you how fast to re-poll. Typical: 3–5 seconds during active streams.
- `liveChatMessages.streamList` — official server-streaming (gRPC) method. Lower latency than polling; the server pushes messages as they arrive rather than requiring repeated requests. **Prefer this for reactive automation** (e.g. Keeper name appears in chat → trigger OBS scene). Source: https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3/live/docs/liveChatMessages/streamList

**OIS Use Cases:**
- Pre-stream checklist bot: verify `madeForKids: false`, `status.privacyStatus`, chat enabled
- Live chat monitor: highlight first-time chatters, trigger Discord alert when stream goes live
- Log SuperChat events to Notion CRM in real time
- Auto-post "Stream is live" message in chat with Notion writing goal for the session

---

### YouTube Analytics API

**What it does:** Access channel and video performance data — views, watch time, subscribers gained, traffic sources, audience demographics.

**Auth:** OAuth 2.0 required.

**Data Latency:** ~2 days. Not real-time.

**Key Dimensions/Metrics:**

| Metric | What It Means |
|---|---|
| `views` | Total views in period |
| `watchTimeMinutes` | Total watch time |
| `averageViewDuration` | Average seconds watched |
| `averageViewPercentage` | % of video watched on average |
| `subscribersGained` | New subscribers from this content |
| `estimatedRevenue` | Revenue (requires monetization) |
| `annotationClickThroughRate` | End screen click-through |

**Traffic Sources:**
`trafficSourceType` dimension shows where viewers came from: YouTube search, suggested, direct, notifications, external, etc.

**OIS Use Cases:**
- Weekly analytics pull → Notion database (views, watch time, new subscribers per video)
- Compare stream VODs vs. short-form clips performance
- Track which ONCE myth content performs best
- Monthly update video data (April 7 first one — pull March data automatically)

