## 2. Discord

### Primary Sources
- **Developer Portal:** https://discord.com/developers/docs
- **REST API Reference:** https://discord.com/developers/docs/reference
- **Gateway (WebSocket) Events:** https://discord.com/developers/docs/topics/gateway
- **Webhooks:** https://discord.com/developers/docs/resources/webhook
- **Permissions Reference:** https://discord.com/developers/docs/topics/permissions
- **Bot Setup Guide:** https://discord.com/developers/docs/getting-started

### What It Is
Two different integration paths with very different complexity levels. Start with webhooks — they require zero infrastructure.

---

### Discord Webhooks (Send-Only, No Bot Required)

**What it is:** A URL you create in Discord that accepts POST requests. No bot, no server, no authentication token management. Just a URL.

**Create one:** Discord Server Settings → Integrations → Webhooks → New Webhook → Copy URL

**What you can send:**
- Plain text messages
- Rich embeds (title, description, color, thumbnail, fields, footer)
- Custom username and avatar per message
- File uploads (images, etc.)
- Buttons and components (limited — needs bot for interactivity)

**Payload Example:**
```json
{
  "username": "The Outside Inn",
  "avatar_url": "https://your-avatar-url.png",
  "embeds": [{
    "title": "🔴 E.I. Werner is LIVE",
    "description": "Writing ONCE mythology live now.",
    "color": 16711680,
    "url": "https://youtube.com/eiwerner",
    "fields": [
      { "name": "Session Goal", "value": "CHOSEN outline — scene 3", "inline": true },
      { "name": "Platform", "value": "YouTube + Twitch", "inline": true }
    ],
    "footer": { "text": "While you're here, you're already there." }
  }]
}
```

**Rate Limit:** 30 requests per minute per webhook URL.

**OIS Use Cases (webhook-only, no infrastructure needed):**
- Stream live alert → `#announcements` channel
- New Keeper joined (from Fourthwall webhook → Pipedream → Discord webhook)
- New Scrivener joined
- ONCE writing milestone hit
- Monthly update video posted

---

### Discord Bot API (Full Read/Write/Manage)

**What it is:** A proper bot application with persistent connection via Gateway WebSocket. Reads events, manages roles, responds to commands, DMs users.

**Auth:** Bot token (generated in Developer Portal). Store securely — never expose.

**Bot Permissions Needed for OIS:**
- `Manage Roles` — assign Scrivener/Keeper roles on membership
- `Send Messages` — welcome messages, announcements
- `Read Message History` — for moderation or monitoring
- `Manage Messages` — moderation
- `Embed Links` — rich message formatting

**Gateway Events (real-time):**
| Event | Trigger |
|---|---|
| `GUILD_MEMBER_ADD` | Someone joins The Outside Inn Discord |
| `MESSAGE_CREATE` | New message posted (for keyword monitoring) |
| `GUILD_MEMBER_UPDATE` | Role or nickname changed |
| `INTERACTION_CREATE` | Slash command used |

**Key REST Endpoints:**
| Endpoint | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `POST /channels/{id}/messages` | Send a message |
| `PUT /guilds/{id}/members/{userId}/roles/{roleId}` | Assign a role |
| `DELETE /guilds/{id}/members/{userId}/roles/{roleId}` | Remove a role |
| `POST /guilds/{id}/members/{userId}/roles` | Batch role update |
| `GET /guilds/{id}/members` | List server members |
| `POST /users/@me/channels` | Open a DM channel |
| `GET /guilds/{id}/roles` | List all roles |

**Rate Limits:** Per-route, typically 5 requests/5 seconds per route. Global limit: 50 requests/second.

**⚠️ Breaking Change — Feb 23, 2026 (verified):**
Discord made several permissions into their own distinct permission bits — they are no longer bundled under broader permissions. Bots that don't explicitly request the new granular permissions will silently lose access to those actions. Affected permissions include:
- `PIN_MESSAGES`
- `CREATE_EVENTS`
- `CREATE_GUILD_EXPRESSIONS`
- (others — check Discord changelog for full list)

**Action required:** If building a bot, update your bot's invite URL to request these permissions explicitly. Check your permission integer. Source: https://docs.discord.com/developers/change-log

**OIS Use Cases:**
- Fourthwall webhook → bot assigns "Scrivener" or "Keeper" Discord role automatically
- Welcome DM to new members with tier-specific info
- Slash command: `/whereami` — returns current ONCE myth progress, next stream date
- Auto-remove role when membership lapses (Fourthwall cancellation webhook → bot removes role)

**Recommended Library:** `discord.py` (Python) or `discord.js` (Node.js). Both well-documented.

---

## 3. Fourthwall

### Primary Sources
- **Docs Hub:** https://docs.fourthwall.com
- **Platform API:** https://docs.fourthwall.com/reference/platform-api
- **Storefront API:** https://docs.fourthwall.com/reference/storefront-api
- **Webhooks:** https://docs.fourthwall.com/reference/webhooks
- **Membership / Subscription Docs:** https://help.fourthwall.com (search "memberships")
- **Discord Integration (native):** https://help.fourthwall.com (search "Discord")

### What It Is
OIS's primary commerce and membership platform. The most important API to wire up. Handles store, memberships, donations, and has a native Discord role sync that may eliminate the need for a custom bot for role assignment.

**⚠️ Important API Status (verified March 2026):**
- The **Open API is explicitly in beta** — treat it as potentially unstable surface area
- **Platform OAuth is invite-only** — you can't self-serve OAuth app registration; the standard path for single-creator automation is API key (Basic Auth), not OAuth
- This means OIS automation = API key auth, not a full OAuth app. Fine for personal use; matters if you ever want to build something others can connect to
- Source: https://docs.fourthwall.com/open-api-beta/

**Merchant Center RSS Feed (public, no auth):**
Fourthwall exposes a public RSS/Atom product feed at a predictable URL for your shop. Useful for read-only product syncing (e.g. pulling product list into Notion) without touching the authenticated API. Source: https://docs.fourthwall.com/open-api-beta/

---

### Fourthwall Platform API

**Auth:** HTTP Basic Auth — use your Fourthwall API credentials (username + password via Base64 encoding). Generate in dashboard under Settings → Integrations.

**Base URL:** `https://openapi.fourthwall.com`

**Rate Limits:** Not publicly specified. Standard REST — don't hammer it.

**Key Resources:**

**Orders:**
```
GET  /v1/orders          — List all orders (paginated)
GET  /v1/orders/{id}     — Get specific order
```
Order object includes: customer name, email, items purchased, price paid, shipping address, status.

**Products:**
```
GET  /v1/products        — List all products
GET  /v1/products/{id}   — Get product details (variants, pricing, inventory)
POST /v1/products        — Create product
PUT  /v1/products/{id}   — Update product
```

**Supporters (Customers/Members):**
```
GET  /v1/supporters      — List supporters
GET  /v1/supporters/{id} — Get supporter detail (email, membership tier, order history)
```

**Memberships:**
```
GET  /v1/memberships     — List membership tiers
GET  /v1/subscriptions   — List all active subscriptions
```

**Mailing Lists:**
```
GET  /v1/mailing-lists          — List available mailing lists
POST /v1/mailing-lists/{id}/subscribe — Add email to list
```

**OIS Use Cases:**
- Pull active Scrivener + Keeper subscriber list → sync to Notion CRM
- Pull new orders → log to Notion for fulfillment tracking
- Check subscriber count for weekly dashboard
- Verify membership status before granting Discord role (if not using native integration)

---

### Fourthwall Storefront API

**Auth:** Public — uses your shop slug, no credentials.

**What it does:** Read-only public-facing product data. Useful for building custom storefronts or embedding product info elsewhere.

**OIS Use Cases:** Minimal. The Platform API is more useful for automation. Storefront API matters if you ever build a custom product page on eiwerner.com.

---

### Fourthwall Webhooks

**This is the most important Fourthwall integration surface.** Webhooks fire events to your endpoint (or a Pipedream/Zapier URL) when things happen in your store.

**Setup:** Dashboard → Settings → Webhooks → Add endpoint URL + select events.

**Security:** Each webhook includes an HMAC-SHA256 signature in the `X-Fourthwall-Signature` header. Verify it to confirm the request is genuine.

**Events:**

| Event | Trigger |
|---|---|
| `ORDER_PLACED` | Any purchase in the store |
| `ORDER_SHIPPED` | Order marked as shipped |
| `ORDER_REFUNDED` | Refund issued |
| `SUBSCRIPTION_CREATED` | New Scrivener or Keeper joins |
| `SUBSCRIPTION_UPDATED` | Membership tier change |
| `SUBSCRIPTION_DELETED` | Membership cancelled or lapsed |
| `DONATION_RECEIVED` | One-time donation |

**SUBSCRIPTION_CREATED Payload (partial):**
```json
{
  "event": "SUBSCRIPTION_CREATED",
  "data": {
    "id": "sub_abc123",
    "supporter": {
      "name": "Jake Hirsch",
      "email": "jake@example.com"
    },
    "tier": {
      "name": "Keeper",
      "price": 21.21
    },
    "created_at": "2026-03-11T10:00:00Z"
  }
}
```

**Native Discord Integration:**
Fourthwall has a native Discord role sync — supporters connect their Discord account and roles are assigned automatically based on membership tier. **Try this first before building a custom bot.** If it covers the use case, skip the custom integration. Check current status at https://help.fourthwall.com.

**No-Code Bridge Options:**
- **Pipedream** — webhook receiver, runs Node.js/Python, free tier sufficient for OIS scale
- **Zapier** — simpler but paid for multi-step zaps
- **n8n** — self-hosted option, more control

**OIS Core Webhook Flow:**
```
Fourthwall SUBSCRIPTION_CREATED
  → Pipedream (receiver)
    → Discord webhook: post to #the-keepers or #scriveners (welcome embed)
    → Notion: create new row in Members database
    → (if Discord bot exists) assign role
```

---

## 4. Patreon (Comparison Reference)

### Primary Sources
- **Developer Portal:** https://www.patreon.com/portal
- **API v2 Docs:** https://docs.patreon.com
- **Webhooks:** https://docs.patreon.com/#webhooks

### Why This Section Exists
For architectural comparison — understanding what Patreon does differently helps clarify why Fourthwall is the right call for OIS, and which Patreon patterns are worth borrowing.

---

### What Patreon Does Well
- Mature membership infrastructure with strong creator trust
- Robust API v2 with member/patron/post/benefit resources
- Native Discord role integration (well-established)
- Large existing audience familiar with Patreon membership model

### What Fourthwall Does That Patreon Doesn't
- Integrated merch store (products + memberships in one platform)
- No Patreon revenue share (Patreon takes 5–12%; Fourthwall takes 0% on memberships with some transaction fees)
- Custom shop experience at your own domain
- Physical product fulfillment built in

### Patreon API v2 Key Differences vs. Fourthwall

| Feature | Patreon | Fourthwall |
|---|---|---|
| Auth | OAuth 2.0 | Basic Auth |
| Member resource | `members` with pledge history | `supporters` with subscription data |
| Post/content API | Yes — can gate posts programmatically | No equivalent |
| Merch integration | None | Native |
| Revenue share | 5–12% | 0% membership, ~3% transaction fee |
| Webhook events | `members:pledge:create/update/delete` | `SUBSCRIPTION_CREATED/UPDATED/DELETED` |

### When Patreon Would Make Sense
If OIS ever pivoted to content-gating (written posts, PDFs, mythology chapter releases) as the primary membership value, Patreon's post API has more infrastructure for that. For the current OIS model — community + merch + stream access — Fourthwall wins.

### Patreon Webhook Pattern (for reference)
```json
{
  "data": {
    "type": "member",
    "id": "patron_id",
    "attributes": {
      "full_name": "Jane Doe",
      "email": "jane@example.com",
      "currently_entitled_amount_cents": 2121,
      "patron_status": "active_patron"
    }
  }
}
```
Patreon webhooks also use HMAC-SHA256 signature verification — same pattern as Fourthwall.

