## 5. OBS WebSocket

### Primary Sources
- **obs-websocket GitHub (v5):** https://github.com/obsproject/obs-websocket
- **Protocol Spec:** https://github.com/obsproject/obs-websocket/blob/master/docs/generated/protocol.md
- **obs-websocket-js (Node.js):** https://github.com/obs-websocket-community-projects/obs-websocket-js
- **obs-websocket Python:** https://github.com/aatikturk/obspython

### What It Is
OBS Studio 28+ has WebSocket built in (port 4455, password protected). It exposes full programmatic control of OBS — scenes, sources, filters, streaming, recording — plus real-time event stream. This is how you make OBS do things without touching the UI.

**v5 is a protocol break from v4** — client libraries written for obs-websocket v4 will not work with v5. Make sure any library you use explicitly supports v5. The `obs-websocket-js` and community Python libraries have v5-specific versions. Source: https://github.com/obsproject/obs-websocket/releases

**Enable it:** OBS → Tools → WebSocket Server Settings → Enable + set password.

---

### Authentication
WebSocket handshake with SHA256-salted password challenge. All client libraries handle this automatically. You just provide host, port, and password.

```javascript
// obs-websocket-js example
const OBSWebSocket = require('obs-websocket-js').default;
const obs = new OBSWebSocket();
await obs.connect('ws://localhost:4455', 'your-password');
```

---

### Key Request Types (what you can ask OBS to do)

**Scene Control:**
| Request | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `GetSceneList` | List all scenes |
| `GetCurrentProgramScene` | Get active scene name |
| `SetCurrentProgramScene` | Switch to a scene by name |
| `CreateScene` | Create a new scene |

**Source Control:**
| Request | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `GetInputList` | List all sources/inputs |
| `SetInputMute` | Mute/unmute an audio source |
| `SetInputVolume` | Set volume level |
| `GetSourceFilterList` | List filters on a source |
| `SetSourceFilterEnabled` | Toggle a filter on/off |

**Text Sources (GDI+ or FreeType):**
```javascript
await obs.call('SetInputSettings', {
  inputName: 'Patron Roll Text',
  inputSettings: { text: 'Welcome, Jake Hirsch — Keeper #3' }
});
```
This is how you update the patron roll text programmatically without touching OBS.

**Browser Sources:**
```javascript
// Reload a browser source (useful after updating HTML overlay content)
await obs.call('PressInputPropertiesButton', {
  inputName: 'Countdown Timer',
  propertyName: 'refreshnocache'
});
```

**Streaming Control:**
| Request | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `GetStreamStatus` | Is stream live? Bytes sent? Duration? |
| `StartStream` | Start streaming |
| `StopStream` | Stop streaming |
| `GetRecordStatus` | Recording active? |
| `StartRecord` / `StopRecord` | Control recording |

**Persistent Storage (OBS 30+):**
```javascript
// Store data that survives OBS restart
await obs.call('SetPersistentData', {
  realm: 'OBS_WEBSOCKET_DATA_REALM_PROFILE',
  slotName: 'streamCount',
  slotValue: 3
});
const data = await obs.call('GetPersistentData', { ... });
```

---

### Key Events (what OBS tells you automatically)

| Event | When It Fires |
|---|---|
| `CurrentProgramSceneChanged` | Scene switched |
| `StreamStateChanged` | Stream started/stopped |
| `RecordStateChanged` | Recording started/stopped |
| `InputMuteStateChanged` | Source muted/unmuted |
| `SceneItemEnableStateChanged` | Source visibility toggled |
| `ExitStarted` | OBS is closing |

```javascript
obs.on('StreamStateChanged', (data) => {
  if (data.outputActive) {
    // Stream just went live — trigger Discord alert
    postDiscordWebhook({ message: '🔴 Stream is live!' });
  }
});
```

---

### OIS Use Cases

**Pre-Stream Checklist Automation:**
```
Script runs before stream:
1. Check YouTube API: madeForKids == false?
2. Check YouTube API: chat enabled?
3. Check OBS: correct scene active?
4. Check OBS: patron roll text up to date?
5. Check OBS: audio levels within range?
Report: ALL CLEAR or list failures
```

**Keeper Celebration Scene:**
```
Fourthwall webhook → new Keeper joined
→ OBS: switch to Keeper celebration scene (duck family animation)
→ OBS: update text source with "[Name] has joined the Keepers"
→ OBS: wait 10 seconds
→ OBS: return to previous scene
```

**Dynamic Patron Roll:**
When a new Scrivener or Keeper pays, update the OBS patron roll text source automatically — no manual editing.

**Session Logging:**
On `StreamStateChanged` (stream ends), log duration, scene switches, and session data to Notion.

