## 8. Anthropic / Claude

### Primary Sources
- **API Docs:** https://docs.anthropic.com
- **Messages API Reference:** https://docs.anthropic.com/en/api/messages
- **Models:** https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/models-overview
- **Tool Use (Function Calling):** https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/tool-use
- **Batch API:** https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/message-batches
- **Files API:** https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/files
- **MCP Protocol:** https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/mcp
- **Claude.ai Projects:** https://support.claude.ai/hc/en-us/articles/projects

### What It Is
The Anthropic API gives you programmatic access to Claude models. For OIS this means: automated content processing, brand consistency checks, mythology analysis, overlay generation, stream recap writing — anything that involves language, judgment, or generation.

**This project (Claude.ai Projects) is a different surface than the API — it's the conversational interface with persistent context. Both are relevant.**

---

### Current Models (March 2026)

| Model | API String | Best For |
|---|---|---|
| Claude Opus 4.6 | `claude-opus-4-6` | Complex reasoning, long documents, brand bible analysis |
| Claude Sonnet 4.6 | `claude-sonnet-4-6` | Balanced — most OIS automation use cases |
| Claude Haiku 4.5 | `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` | Fast, cheap — high-volume simple tasks |

**Context Window:** 200K tokens standard. 1M token window available with beta header.

---

### Messages API

**Auth:** `x-api-key` header with your API key from console.anthropic.com.

**Base URL:** `https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages`

**Basic Request:**
```javascript
const response = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'x-api-key': process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
    'anthropic-version': '2023-06-01'
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
    max_tokens: 1024,
    messages: [
      { role: 'user', content: 'Your prompt here' }
    ]
  })
});
```

**System Prompts:**
```javascript
{
  model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
  max_tokens: 1024,
  system: 'You are the OIS brand assistant. The brand voice is: warm but not soft, direct over diplomatic, earnest without being naïve...',
  messages: [{ role: 'user', content: '...' }]
}
```

**Rate Limits:** Tier-based. Starting tier: ~60 requests/minute, ~100K tokens/minute. Increases with usage and/or paid tier upgrade.

---

### Tool Use (Function Calling)

Claude can call tools you define — useful for having Claude decide when to look something up, update Notion, or trigger an action.

```javascript
{
  tools: [{
    name: 'log_to_notion',
    description: 'Log stream session data to the Notion stream database',
    input_schema: {
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        date: { type: 'string' },
        duration_minutes: { type: 'number' },
        writing_goal: { type: 'string' },
        notes: { type: 'string' }
      },
      required: ['date', 'writing_goal']
    }
  }],
  tool_choice: { type: 'auto' }
}
```

When Claude uses a tool, you get a `tool_use` block in the response. You execute the tool, then pass the result back for Claude to continue.

---

### Batch API

For non-real-time processing at 50% cost reduction.

```javascript
POST /v1/messages/batches
{
  "requests": [
    {
      "custom_id": "stream-recap-20260311",
      "params": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "max_tokens": 500,
        "messages": [{ "role": "user", "content": "Write a stream recap for..." }]
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Process up to 10,000 requests per batch. Results available within 24 hours (usually much faster). Use for: weekly content analysis, monthly report generation, bulk mythology consistency checks.

---

### Files API (Beta)

Upload files once, reference by ID across multiple messages. Up to 350MB per file.

```javascript
// Upload brand bible once
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append('file', fs.createReadStream('brand-bible.md'));
formData.append('purpose', 'assistants');

const uploadResponse = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/files', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'x-api-key': process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY },
  body: formData
});
const { id: fileId } = await uploadResponse.json();

// Reference it in messages without re-uploading
messages: [{
  role: 'user',
  content: [
    { type: 'document', source: { type: 'file', file_id: fileId } },
    { type: 'text', text: 'Is this stream description consistent with the brand voice?' }
  ]
}]
```

---

### MCP (Model Context Protocol)

MCP is an open standard that lets Claude connect to external tools and data sources during a conversation. The OIS project already has Google Calendar and Gmail MCP servers connected.

**How it works:** MCP servers expose tools (functions Claude can call). Claude decides when to use them based on context.

**Already connected to this project:**
- Google Calendar MCP — `https://gcal.mcp.claude.com/mcp`
- Gmail MCP — `https://gmail.mcp.claude.com/mcp`

**Other useful MCP servers:**
- Notion MCP — `https://github.com/makenotion/notion-mcp-server` (connect your OIS Notion workspace)
- GitHub MCP — for overlay code repositories

**Use in API calls:**
```javascript
{
  model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
  max_tokens: 1000,
  messages: [{ role: 'user', content: 'Add a reminder for the Marwan call Friday at 2pm' }],
  mcp_servers: [
    { type: 'url', url: 'https://gcal.mcp.claude.com/mcp', name: 'google-calendar' }
  ]
}
```

---

### Claude.ai Projects — How It Differs from API

| Feature | Claude.ai Project | Anthropic API |
|---|---|---|
| Interface | Chat UI (this) | Programmatic HTTP |
| Context | Project files persist across chats | Each call is stateless (you manage history) |
| Auth | Your Claude.ai account | API key |
| Use case | Brand strategy, document work, thinking partner | Automation, integrations, production pipelines |
| Cost | Claude.ai subscription | Per-token pricing |
| MCP | Connected via project settings | Passed in request |

**This project (OIS Brand Bible as project file) is the strategic brain.** The API is the automation muscle. They're complementary.

---

### OIS API Use Cases

**Brand Voice Checker:**
```
Input: stream description draft
System: [brand voice guidelines from brand bible]
Output: revised version + specific notes on what was off-brand
```

**Stream Recap Generator:**
```
Input: stream duration, writing goal, ONCE progress, viewer count
Output: formatted recap ready to post in Discord #session-notes
```

**ONCE Consistency Checker:**
```
Input: new CHOSEN outline section
System: [ONCE mythology established in ONCE + MOTHER + BROTHER + WAR + GATE]
Output: consistency check — does this contradict anything established?
```

**Monthly Update Video Script:**
```
Input: Notion stream sessions data for the month
Output: First draft script for April 7 monthly update video
```

**HTML Overlay Development (established working pattern):**
The Broadcast Alpha overlays (countdown timer, patron roll) were built via Claude pair-programming. This pattern is proven and repeatable. Use for all future OBS overlay work.

