## 9. Cross-Platform Integration Chains

### Chain 1: New Keeper Joins

```
Trigger: Fourthwall SUBSCRIPTION_CREATED (tier: Keeper)
  ↓
Step 1: Pipedream receiver validates HMAC signature
  ↓
Step 2: Discord webhook → #the-keepers
  Embed: "[Name] has joined the Keepers. Kept, we keep on."
  Duck family animation note in embed
  ↓
Step 3: Notion API → Members CRM
  Create row: name, email, tier, join date, founding number
  ↓
Step 4 (if stream is live): OBS WebSocket
  Switch to Keeper celebration scene
  Update text source: "[Name] has joined the Keepers"
  Return to stream after 10 seconds
  ↓
Step 5: OBS WebSocket (async)
  Update patron roll text with new Keeper name
```

---

### Chain 2: New Scrivener Joins

```
Trigger: Fourthwall SUBSCRIPTION_CREATED (tier: Scrivener)
  ↓
Step 1: Pipedream validates webhook
  ↓
Step 2: Discord webhook → #scriveners
  Embed: "[Name] has wet their quill. Welcome, Scrivener."
  ↓
Step 3: Notion → Members CRM row created
  ↓
Step 4 (if stream is live): OBS → Scrivener welcome scene
  Typewriter animation, 8 seconds, return
  ↓
Step 5: OBS → update patron roll with Scrivener name
```

---

### Chain 3: Pre-Stream Checklist

```
Trigger: Manual (run script 10 min before stream)
  ↓
Check 1: YouTube Data API
  liveBroadcasts: madeForKids == false?
  liveBroadcasts: status.lifeCycleStatus?
  liveBroadcasts: enableLiveChatReplay == true?
  ↓
Check 2: OBS WebSocket
  Current scene == Outside Inn Warmup?
  Patron roll text source up to date?
  All audio sources unmuted?
  ↓
Check 3: Notion API
  Today's writing goal populated?
  ↓
Output: Terminal report
  ✅ ALL CLEAR — stream when ready
  ❌ ISSUES: [list each failure]
```

---

### Chain 4: Stream Goes Live → Community Alert

```
Trigger: OBS Event — StreamStateChanged (outputActive: true)
  ↓
Step 1: YouTube Live Streaming API
  Get liveBroadcastId and liveChatId
  Post chat message: "Writing goal today: [pull from Notion] | Writing, fantasy, and games are destinations."
  ↓
Step 2: Discord webhook → #stream-alerts
  Embed: "🔴 Live now | [writing goal] | [YouTube link] | [Twitch link]"
  ↓
Step 3: Notion → Stream Sessions
  Create new row with date, goal (populate duration when stream ends)
```

---

### Chain 5: Stream Ends → Session Logging

```
Trigger: OBS Event — StreamStateChanged (outputActive: false)
  ↓
Step 1: YouTube Analytics API (queued — 2-day delay)
  Schedule pull of peak viewers, watch time, new subscribers
  ↓
Step 2: Claude API → Stream Recap
  Input: session duration, writing goal, scene switch log
  Output: 2-paragraph recap for Discord
  ↓
Step 3: Notion → update Stream Sessions row
  Duration, recap text
  ↓
Step 4: Discord webhook → #session-notes
  Post Claude-generated recap
```

---

### Chain 6: ONCE Milestone Completion

```
Trigger: Notion webhook — ONCE Goals database row updated
  Filter: Status changed to "Complete"
  ↓
Step 1: Extract milestone name (e.g., "CHOSEN [Outline]")
  ↓
Step 2: Discord webhook → #outside-inn (public channel)
  Embed: "✅ CHOSEN [Outline] Complete | 6/7 myths outlined"
  ↓
Step 3: Notion → Brand Bible page
  Append block with completion date
  ↓
Step 4 (if scheduled): Claude API
  Generate social post for next video/clip using milestone as hook
```

---

## 10. Build Order & Philosophy

### The Philosophy

Every integration must serve one of three purposes:
1. **Reduce manual work on stream day** — fewer things to forget, fewer things to check
2. **Make community feel seen** — instant, branded responses when members join
3. **Capture data that improves next stream** — log everything, review monthly

Build the cheapest valuable thing first. Then layer.

---

### Recommended Build Order

**Phase 1 — Before Wednesday March 11 (if possible)**

| # | Integration | Complexity | Value |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Fourthwall → Discord webhook (Pipedream) | Low | High — Keeper/Scrivener alerts |
| 2 | Fourthwall native Discord role sync | Zero | High — try this first |
| 3 | YouTube → Discord webhook (stream live alert) | Low | High — community awareness |

**Phase 2 — First Month Athens**

| # | Integration | Complexity | Value |
|---|---|---|---|
| 4 | Fourthwall → Notion Members CRM | Low | High — CRM foundation |
| 5 | OBS WebSocket pre-stream checklist script | Medium | Critical — never miss a check again |
| 6 | YouTube Analytics → Notion (weekly cron) | Medium | Medium — weekly dashboard |

**Phase 3 — April/May**

| # | Integration | Complexity | Value |
|---|---|---|---|
| 7 | OBS WebSocket → Keeper/Scrivener celebration scenes | Medium | High — on-stream moments |
| 8 | Streamlabs Socket → OBS scene triggers | Medium | Medium — follow/sub events |
| 9 | Claude API → stream recap generator | Low | Medium — saves time |
| 10 | Notion MCP → Claude Project | Low | High — brand bible Q&A |

---

### Tools Needed

| Tool | Role | Cost |
|---|---|---|
| Pipedream | Webhook receiver + automation logic | Free tier sufficient |
| OBS Studio 28+ | Already installed | Free |
| obs-websocket-js or obspython | OBS control library | Free |
| Anthropic API key | Claude API access | Pay per use |
| Notion Integration | Already available | Free |
| Fourthwall API credentials | From dashboard | Free |

---

### No-Infrastructure Starting Point

Before writing a single line of code:
1. **Fourthwall → Discord:** Set up native Discord integration in Fourthwall dashboard. If that handles role assignment, you're done with that chain at zero complexity.
2. **Fourthwall → Discord webhook (Pipedream):** Create a Pipedream workflow with a Fourthwall webhook trigger → Discord webhook step. No server. No deployment. 15 minutes.
3. **YouTube live alert:** When stream goes live, manually paste link in Discord. Automate later.

Get the simple wins first. The complex chains build on a foundation of simpler ones working reliably.

